               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 10 works (a-j)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous Arabic and Persian works on Sufism and doctrine, comprised of various tractates assembled from different sources of different dates. Volume not dated; items a dated to 14 Jumādá II 1101/25 March 1690, with portions of the volume dating slightly earlier. Variable nastaʿlīq and shikastah āmīz hands. Stamped foliation. Lacks original binding; later leather boards with red and yellow combed-marbled doublures. Folios unbound; cropped, later repairs, stains, and wormholes. Condition, extremely fragile. IOL microfilm 3266. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="24v">ff. 1v-24v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī treatise on conceptions of God, the universe, and man’s destiny in this world and the hereafter, by Shaykh Saʿd al-Dīn Maḥmūd ibn ʿAbd al-Karīm Shabistarī (d. 720/1320). 
</p>
                        <p>The work consists of eight bāb.  </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 24v): completed 14 Jumādá II 1101/25 March 1690. 
</p>
                        <p>According to a detailed note (f. 1r), the work was copied from a manuscript corrected and partially written by the saint and scholar, ʿAbd al-Raḥmān Aḥmad "Jāmī", who dated it to the avāʾil (first ten days) of Jumādá II 862/April 1458. 
There is remarkable variation in the quality and fluency of the nastaʿlīq hand, occasionally tending to shikastah, indicating this is not the work of a professional scribe, but copied for private use. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1365">Ḥaqq al-yaqīn fī maʿrifat Rabb al-ʿālamīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_1365">حقّ اليقين فى معرفة ربّ العالمين</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_107030610"> Shabistarī, Maḥmūd ibn ʿAbd al-Karīm, -approximately 1320</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_107030610">شبستري، محمود بن عبد الكريم</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item2">
                     <locus from="25v" to="60v">ff. 25v-60v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_187568969">Ilāh'ābādī, Muḥibb Allāh</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_187568969">شيخ محبّ الله الٰه آبادى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21695">Sharḥ-i Risālat al-tasvīyat bayna al-ifādat va al-qubūl</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21695">شرح رسالة التسويّة بين الافادة و القبول</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Persian commentary on the Arabic Ṣūfī treatise, <title>Risālat al-tasvīyat bayna al-ifādat va al-qubūl</title>, treating the unity of God, by the Indian Ṣūfī saint, Shaykh Muḥibb Allāh Ilāhābādī (d. 1058/1648).  
                        </p>
                        <p>The present copy begins with the rare preface. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Multiple hands, ranging from a neat nastaʿlīq hand occasionally tending towards shikastah, to a rough Indian taʿlīq hand. Iron-rich ink changing to a less caustic medium on folio 46 onward. 
</p>
                        <p>Arabic annotations in margins, occasionally cropped. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item3">
                     <locus from="61v" to="79v">ff. 61v-79v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Arabic treatise on the relationship between logic and religious doctrine by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins; though cropped, a few have been folded in, revealing the extent of original margins prior to being cropped. Upper edge torn. 
</p>
                        <p>Extensive Arabic notes at beginning. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21696">Risālat tajvīzīyat ḥāvīyat li-al-dalāʾil al-ʿaqlīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21696">رسالة تجويزيّة حاويّة لالدّلائل العقليّة</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item4">
                     <locus from="80r" to="81r">ff. 80r-81r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Untitled extract from an Arabic treatise on Sunni tradition by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item5">
                     <locus from="82r" to="83v ">ff. 82r-83v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. </p>
                        <p>Untitled anecdote on inter-sectarian debates on respective concepts of imamate selected from the maqālāt or maxims of Ḥāfiẓ ʿInāyat Allāh, alive at the time of writing. </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Transcribed obliquely in a squat shikastah āmīz hand. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7145">Ḥāfiẓ ʿInāyat Allāh</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7145">حافظ عنايت الله</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item6">
                     <locus from="84v" to="86v">ff. 84v-86v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item f. </p>
                        <p>Untitled Arabic treatise on diction in religious works by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The work terminates with the mention of Miyān Shaykh Muḥammad, but it is not clear if he is connected with the composition of the work or with the scribe. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Transcribed obliquely in a squat shikastah āmīz hand. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item7">
                     <locus from="86v" to="90r">ff. 86v-90r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="per">Arabic and Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item g. </p>
                        <p>Untitled Ṣūfī treatise largely in Arabic, but interspersed sparsely with Persian, by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Transcribed obliquely in a squat shikastah āmīz hand. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item8">
                     <locus from="90v" to="104v">ff. 90v-104v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="per">Arabic and Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item h. Catalogued as no. 1287 by Storey, Arabic MSS in IOL, vol. i (1930), where it is incorrectly cited as Delhi Persian 1167g. </p>
                        <p>Extracts from the encyclopaedia of theosophical doctrine, al-Futūḥāt al-Makkīyah, by Ibn al-ʿArabī (d. 638/1240). 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Transcribed in irregular alternating pages of oblique and horizontal squat shikastah āmīz by multiple hands. 
</p>
                        <p>The selection of passages is occasionally interrupted by comments or passages quoted from unidentified Persian works. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_5047">al-Futūḥāt al-Makkīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_5047">الفتوحات المكّيّة</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_95223177" type="supplied">Ibn al-ʿArabī (d. 638/1240)</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_95223177" type="supplied">ابن العربى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="9" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item9">
                     <locus from="105v" to="106v">ff. 105v-106v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item i. </p>
                        <p>Unidentified Arabic ghazal on religious themes mentioning the author’s name in the terminal verse, Muḥyī al-Dīn, that is, Muḥyī al-Dīn Ibn al-ʿArabī (d. 638/1240). 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_95223177" type="supplied">Muḥyī al-Dīn Ibn al-ʿArabī (d. 638/1240)</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_95223177" type="supplied">محيى الدّين</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="10" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1167-item10">
                     <locus from="107v" to="173v">ff. 107v-173v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item j. Catalogued as no. 1394 by Storey, Arabic MSS in IOL, vol. i (1930), where it is incorrectly cited as Delhi Persian 1167h. </p>
                        <p>Incomplete copy of the Arabic Ṣūfī treatise <title>ʿAqāʾid al-khavāṣṣ</title> ascribed here to the Indian Ṣūfī saint, Shaykh Muḥibb Allāh Ilāhābādī (d. 1058/1648). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work ends abruptly after the rubric for the sixteenth of the twenty-one daqāʾiq or points of detail (each enumerated) making up the original work. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21697">ʿAqāʾid al-khavāṣṣ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21697">عقائد الخواصّ</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_187568969" type="supplied">Shaykh Muḥibb Allāh Ilāh'ābādī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_187568969" type="supplied">شيخ محبّ الله الٰه آبادى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
